  "text": "Using cardiac CT, Dalen and colleagues [CITATION_1] demonstrated the prevalence of HALT and reduced leaflet motion (RLM) in surgically implanted Perceval sutureless aortic valve bioprostheses, even in patients on anticoagulation. It has been hypothesized that HALT and RLM may be caused by subclinical leaflet thrombosis, leading to premature SVD and risk of thromboemboli [CITATION_2] .",
